      <Desc>THE PRIMARY PURPOSE OF THE ORGANIZATION IS TO PROVIDE FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE TO THE COUNTY OF SACRAMENTO BY FINANCING THE ACQUISITION, CONSTRUCTION, IMPROVEMENT, AND REMODELING OF PUBLIC BUILDINGS, FACILITIES, AND EQUIPMENT. A.2003 COP (JUVENILE COURTHOUSE PROJECTS) TO FINANCE THE CONSTRUCTION OF A NEW THREE-STORY JUVENILE COURTHOUSE (LOCATED AT THE CORNER OF BRANCH CENTER ROAD AND KIEFER BOULEVARD, 99,456 SQUARE FEET) CONSISTING OF SIX COURTROOMS (AND SPACE FOR TWO ADDITIONAL COURTROOMS FOR FUTURE EXPANSION), SUPPORT SERVICES AREAS (HOLDING CELL AREAS, ATTORNEY CONFERENCE ROOMS, JUDGES CHAMBERS AND COURT CLERK AREA) AND ADMINISTRATIVE SUPPORT SERVICES AREAS (FOR COURT AND SHERIFFS STAFF, COURT RECORDS, CHILD WAITING AREA, AND PUBLIC WAITING AREAS). B. 2018 REFUNDING COP TO REFUND AND RETIRE ALL OUTSTANDING PRINCIPAL AMOUNTS OF THE COUNTY'S 1997 REFUNDING COP, 2003 COP (PUBLIC FACILITIES PROJECTS), 2006 COP (PUBLIC FACILITIES FINANCING), AND 2007 COP (ANIMAL CARE/YOUTH DETENTION PROJECTS), FUND THE RESERVE FUND, AND PAY THE COST OF FINANCING.C. 2020 REFUNDING COP TO REFUND AND RETIRE ALL OUTSTANDING PRINCIPAL AMOUNTS OF THE COUNTY'S 2010 REFUNDING COP, FUND THE RESERVE FUND, AND PAY THE COST OF FINANCING.D. 2020 SUNRISE REFUNDING COP TO REFUND AND RETIRE ALL OUTSTANDING PRINCIPAL AMOUNTS OF SUNRISE 2007 COP, AND PAY THE COST OF FINANCING.</Desc>
